THE entire block around the Cash Crusaders shop in central Cape Town is on lockdown this afternoon in an apparent hostage situation.While Western Cape police had yet to provide details, it is understood that armed robbers had entered the store and not allowed staff to leave.Smoke was seen coming from inside the store. A fire truck arrived at the scene shortly afterwards.Central City Improvement District security manager Mo Hendricks said that a SAPS task force was dealing with the matter.He said officials were assisting by closing off the entire block to the public.The affected streets are Long, Strand, Loop, Castle and Riebeek.&ldquo;We want to create a safe perimeter around the scene because if a suspect gets out, they could mingle and get into the crowd,&rdquo; he said.They also wanted members of the public to be a safe distance away should something happen.Metro police were at the scene to divert traffic.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/hostage-situation-locks-down-cape-town-cbd-streets-20170705Avoid Strand Street in Cape Town, there is currently a robbery and hostage situation underway at Cash Crusaders. #sabcnews pic.twitter.com/rk5f9X49qh&mdash; Sheldon Cameron (@Sheldon_Cameron) July 5, 2017Footage of hostages being released at Cash Crusaders Robbery in Cape Town CBD. Suspects were apprehended. ?? Jolandi M pic.twitter.com/dDRaUEbr5Q&mdash; Brandon Booysen (@Boyas112) July 5, 2017#CBDrobbery A task team has moved into the Cash Crusaders. IM pic.twitter.com/so90FqjHht&mdash; EWN Reporter (@ewnreporter) July 5, 2017Firemen entering Cash Crusaders,filled with smoke after #CBDRobbery turned hostage drama. Cops push ppl back, saying robbers still inside. pic.twitter.com/JUlkYxuxhF&mdash; Chantall Presence (@ChazPrez) July 5, 2017Specialized security force leaves cash crusaders, fire fighters enter. Store appears to have been cleared. #CTrobbery pic.twitter.com/ykiDDvxmps&mdash; James de Villiers (@pejames) July 5, 2017